  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      There are few studies evaluating the value of 3D echocardiography in children undergoing
      congenital cardiac surgery. The aim of this observational study is to describe common and
      uncommon congenital malformations with the help of 3D echo and compare the findings and the
      measurements with those obtained with conventional 2D echo.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
